**1. Passive Recon (High‑Intensity OSINT)**
whois: whois example.com  
dig: dig example.com ANY  
dig MX: dig example.com mx  
dig AAAA: dig example.com AAAA  
nslookup: nslookup example.com  
dnsrecon: dnsrecon -d example.com  
theHarvester: theHarvester -d example.com  
wafw00f: wafw00f https://example.com

**2. Subdomain Enumeration (Broad Surface Discovery)**
subfinder: subfinder -d example.com -all  
amass: amass enum -passive -d example.com  
github-subdomains: github-subdomains -d example.com  
gitlab-subdomains: gitlab-subdomains -d example.com  
analyticsrelationships: analyticsrelationships -d example.com

**3. DNS Resolution (High‑Accuracy Filtering)**
dnsx: dnsx -d example.com -resp -a -aaaa -cname  
puredns: puredns resolve subs.txt -r resolvers.txt  
dnstake: dnstake enum --domain example.com  
dsieve: dsieve -d example.com

**4. Live Host Detection (Aggressive Probing)**
httpx: httpx -l resolved.txt -status-code -title -tech-detect -cdn -ip  
smap: smap example.com  
nmap (manual): nmap -sV example.com

**5. URL & Content Discovery (Deep Crawling)**
katana: katana -u https://example.com -d 5 -js-crawl  
hakrawler: hakrawler -url https://example.com  
gau: gau example.com  
waybackurls: waybackurls example.com  
urlfinder: urlfinder -d example.com  
subjs: subjs -i urls.txt  
jsluice: jsluice analyze script.js  
sourcemapper: sourcemapper -i script.js.map

**6. JavaScript & Endpoint Analysis (Aggressive JS Recon)**
unfurl: unfurl keys < urls.txt  
jsluice: jsluice analyze script.js  
subjs: subjs -i urls.txt

**7. Parameter Discovery (High‑Coverage Input Mapping)**
gf: gf xss < urls.txt  
qsreplace: cat params.txt | qsreplace  
gotator: gotator -sub example -perm perms.txt

**8. Behavior Analysis (High‑Signal Testing)**
nomore403: nomore403 -u https://example.com  
Web-Cache-Vulnerability-Scanner: python3 scanner.py -u https://example.com  
ppmap: ppmap -u https://example.com  
crlfuzz: crlfuzz -u https://example.com  
dalfox: dalfox url https://example.com

**9. Manual Fuzzing (Controlled Exploration)**
ffuf: ffuf -u https://example.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt  
VhostFinder: VhostFinder -u https://example.com

**10. Vulnerability Scanning (Manual Trigger Only)**
nuclei: nuclei -u https://example.com

**11. Utilities (Workflow Enhancers)**
anew: cat new.txt | anew all.txt  
notify: notify -bulk  
enumerepo: enumerepo -d example.com  
interactsh-client: interactsh-client  
mapcidr: mapcidr -cidr cidrs.txt  
sns: sns -d example.com  
cent: cent -u https://example.com  
mantra: mantra -u https://example.com
